  "description": [
    "FROM PEACE TO WAR Spain Severed the Diplomatic Re lations Before She Received the Ultimatum GAVE GEN WOODFORD HIS PASSPORTS North Atlantic Squadron Moves to the Enemys CountryInspiring Scenes in Key West HarborBig Warships Flash Night Messages Across the SkiesNo Interpreter Needed to Tell That They Heant Hostile Actions Fleet floves Undercover of Night A despatch from Washington saysWar between the United States and Spain is a fact though not yet officially declared so by Congress The stirring events of Thursday culminated in the afternoon in orders for the departure of the North Atlantic squadron to blockade Havana This is practically an act of war so that the war between this country and Spain may truly be said to date from April 21 1893 A few minutes after the opening of the State Department came word from Minister Woodford that the Spanish government had notified him before he could present Presi dent McKinleys ultimatum that it had broken off diplomatic relations with the United States General Woodfords cable gram also stated that he had then asked for his passports and was about to leave Madrid The administration in a public statement soon afterward announced that it regarded the action of"
